{
  "texts": [
    "Model implementation Baseline modelsWe used 2048-bit Morgan fingerprints with radius 3 and total counts for representing peptides smiles to the models which is a robust choice for peptide representations.",
    "We trained, GP with GAK [4], Random Forest [33], XGBoost [34] and fine-tuned ChemBerta [12] as baseline models for the applicability domain aware setting.",
    "We tuned models in inner loops validation split and used the best hyper parameters on validation set and reported the model performance on the test results.",
    "in setting B, We compared the results on pre-specified benchmarks in [3] including RF [33], SVM [35], AttentiveFP [16], DMPNN [17], GAT [36], GCN [37], MPNN [15], PAGTN [38], RNN [39], LSTM [40], GRU [41], ChemCeption [42], ImageMol [43], Multi-CycGT [44] and MUCoCP [45].",
    "Results Setting A: applicability-domain-aware splitsWe evaluate two leakage-controlled protocols: (i) label-stratified splits and (ii) canonical-group-stratified splits that remove near-duplicates."
  ]
}